h-borders($width, $lines, $font-size, $border-style): Alias for horizontal-borders mixin.

horizontal-borders($width, $lines, $font-size, $border-style): Apply both leading and trailing borders.

leader($lines, $font-size, $property): Apply leading whitespace. The $property can be margin or padding.

leading-border($width, $lines, $font-size, $border-style): Apply a leading border. $border-style and $width are deprecated and will be removed in a future version of Compass.

link-colors($normal, $hover, $active, $visited, $focus)

margin-trailer($lines, $font-size): Apply trailing whitespace as margin.

padding-leader($lines, $font-size): Apply leading whitespace as padding.

padding-trailer($lines, $font-size): Apply trailing whitespace as padding.

margin-leader($lines, $font-size): Apply leading whitespace as margin.

min-height($value): Cross browser min-height mixin.

min-width($value): Cross browser min-width mixin.

opacity($opacity): Provides cross-browser CSS opacity. Takes a number between 0 and 1 as the argument, e.g. 0.5 for 50% opacity.

opaque: Make an element completely opaque.

trailer($lines, $font-size, $property): Apply trailing whitespace. The $property can be margin or padding.

rhythm($leader, $padding-leader, $padding-trailer, $trailer, $font-size): Shorthand mixin to apply whitespace for top and bottom margins and padding.

rhythm-margins($leader, $trailer, $font-size): Shorthand mixin to apply whitespace for top and bottom margins.

rhythm-padding($padding-leader, $padding-trailer, $font-size): Shorthand mixin to apply whitespace for top and bottom padding.

rhythm-borders($width, $lines, $font-size, $border-style): Apply borders and whitespace equally to all sides.

single-box-shadow($hoff, $voff, $blur, $spread, $color, $inset): Provides a single cross-browser CSS box shadow for Webkit, Gecko, and CSS3. Includes default arguments for color, horizontal offset, vertical offset, blur length, spread length, and inset.

trailing-border($width, $lines, $font-size, $border-style): Apply a trailing border.

transparent: Make an element completely transparent.

unstyled-link: A link that looks and acts like the text it is contained within

word-break($value): Mixin for word-break properties, legal values for $type : normal, keep-all, break-all

